lindsey martins msw is a pediatric medical social worker at lucile packard children's hospital lindsey martins msw is a pediatric medical social worker at lucile packard children's hospital she has been a medical social worker since 2007 she started her career with a one year fellowship program in the picu cvicu following the fellowship she provided six months of coverage for the nephrology service covering dialysis and transplant in april of 2008 she started working with both pediatric and adult cystic fibrosis patients and now her primary focus is with the pediatric cystic fibrosis pulmonary and allergy immunology patients lindsey is currently participating in the cystic fibrosis foundation social work mentoring program she also facilitates the pals program at stanford university
